        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName}'s psychotic symptoms began in early adulthood and have been present for about 6 years, which is compatible with the usual age range for onset of schizophrenia [MEDDIALOG:F20.9:7, MEDLINEPLUS:F20.9]. Early symptoms included believing that people were after him, and over time he developed stronger persecutory ideas, social withdrawal, and inability to sustain employment [MEDDIALOG:F20.9:7, MEDLINEPLUS:F20.9]. He has had prior psychiatric hospitalizations for suicidal threat and attempt [MEDDIALOG:F20.9:7].\n\nFamily reports that {patientName} has at times refused therapy or medication despite persistent symptoms [MEDDIALOG:F20.9:7]. He has no clearly documented chronic nonpsychiatric medical illness in the provided evidence [MEDDIALOG:F20.9:7]. Current treatment is modeled as outpatient antipsychotic management, since medicine can help control many symptoms and patients may need trials of different medicines to find the best response [MEDLINEPLUS:F20.9]. He denies alcohol or illicit substance misuse; this is a clinically plausible default because the evidence is silent on substance use."
          }
        ]
      }
